As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 237 people, 57 households, and 49 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{convert|39.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 71 housing units at an average density of 11.9 per square mile (4.6/km{{sup|2}}). The racial makeup of the CDP was 96.20% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 1.27% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 1.69% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.84% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 2.95% of the population.

There were 57 households, out of which 63.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 42.1% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 40.4% had a female householder with no husband present, and 12.3% were non-families. 7.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 3.5% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 4.16 and the average family size was 4.34.

In the CDP, the population was spread out, with 49.8% under the age of 18, 9.7% from 18 to 24, 26.2% from 25 to 44, 8.0% from 45 to 64, and 6.3% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 18 years. For every 100 females, there were 106.1 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 88.9 males.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $11,786, and the median income for a family was $11,429. Males had a median income of $15,750 versus $45,417 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $4,260. About 67.9% of families and 72.6% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 72.2% of those under the age of 18 and 100.0% of those 65 or over.

